notesStmt.note: Folio [ii recto] (modern paper flyleaf) contains a Hebrew description of the contents of this volume. A German description of the manuscript from Moritz Steinschneider's catalogue is glued to folio [ii verso].
A note of sale, recording Eliyahu ben Shelomoh and Ḳerapula (?) bat Benyamin, folio 1r.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 31; written lines: 31; Running title on each recto. Visible ruling with a hard-point.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental semi-cursive script of the 16th century.
